${project.name}

  The Bonita Project plugin provides the capability to handle Bonita specific actions. It
  can build BDM artifacts and analyze the project dependencies to find Bonita specific extensions.

* Goals Overview

  The Bonita Project plugin has several goals:

  *{{{./analyze-mojo.html}bonita-project:analyze}} analyzes the dependencies of this project and determines which are Bonita specific
  among connectors, actor fitlers, rest api extensions, themes or custom pages.
  
  *{{{./business-archive-mojo.html}bonita-project:business-archive}} build *.proc files into Bonita Business Achive files.
  
  *{{{./copy-provided-pages-mojo.html}bonita-project:copy-provided-pages}} detects and copy provided Bonita web pages.

  *{{{./create-bdm-module-mojo.html}bonita-project:create-bdm-module}} adds a child 'bdm' maven module to a Bonita Project.
  
  *{{{./create-extensions-module-mojo.html}bonita-project:create-extensions-module}} adds a child 'extensions' maven module to a Bonita Project.
  
  *{{{./extract-configuration-mojo.html}bonita-project:extract-configuration}} extract the parameters values from a given Bonita Configuration file.

  *{{{./generate-bdm-dao-client-mojo.html}bonita-project:generate-bdm-dao-client}} generates dao-client java sources for a given BDM descriptor.

  *{{{./generate-bdm-model-mojo.html}bonita-project:generate-bdm-model}} generates model java sources for a given BDM descriptor.

  *{{{./help-mojo.html}bonita-project:help}} Display help information on bonita-project-maven-plugin.

  *{{{./install-mojo.html}bonita-project:install}} install project local dependencies in the local repository.
  
  *{{{./merge-configuration-mojo.html}bonita-project:merge-configuration}} merge additional parameters values into a given Bonita Configuration file.
  
  *{{{./uid-page-mojo.html}bonita-project:uid-page}} build UI Designer pages.
  
  *{{{./validate-mojo.html}bonita-project:validate}} validate Bonita project models and descriptors.
